From: melnoff <melnoff360@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 25 Apr 2026 15:41:56 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] feat(ui): redesign VLESS proxy form
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

- URL input is now multi-line (5-line min, auto-grow up to ~12
  lines, then scroll). Long vless:// URLs are no longer cropped.
- Below the URL, a flat list of editable parameter fields:
  server, port, uuid, flow, security, sni, alpn, fingerprint,
  reality public key, reality short ID, transport, path, host,
  gRPC service name, header type, name, allowInsecure checkbox.
- Two-way sync: editing the URL repopulates the fields; editing
  any field rebuilds the URL. A guard flag breaks the loop so
  setText calls don't re-trigger the opposite direction.
- Adds MTP::Proxy::BuildVlessUrl() — inverse of ParseVlessUrl().

The URL field still drives saving (collectData uses the URL text),
so all backend code paths are unchanged.
